        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 7:07PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 707 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Sweetwater Creek State Park to near
Arnco-Sargent, and moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Newnan, Douglasville, City of South Fulton, Sandy Springs,
Smyrna, Fairburn, Austell, Palmetto, Whitesburg, Chattahoochee Hill,
Lithia Springs, East Newnan, Midtown, Plant Yates, Vinings, Dunaway
Gardens, Cascade Heights, Campbellton, and Sandtown.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
